WEBVTT

00:05.705 --> 00:07.573
Shannon, what are you doing?

00:07.641 --> 00:09.808
There's, like,
20 Goldfish behind the couch.

00:09.877 --> 00:11.977
I know. I'm so bad at this.

00:12.046 --> 00:14.079
Pick up the Goldfish and go get ready.

00:14.148 --> 00:15.748
We're going to Nick's parents'
for dinner.

00:15.816 --> 00:17.449
Yeah, you mind if I pass?

00:17.518 --> 00:19.385
I read this warning on the
Internet of the dangers

00:19.453 --> 00:23.222
of kids getting high on nutmeg,
and I want to try it.

00:23.290 --> 00:24.890
You're going.

00:24.959 --> 00:26.358
Walt needs our feedback.

00:26.427 --> 00:29.361
He's auditioning for a new play
about an out of control cop

00:29.430 --> 00:30.696
with no morals.

00:30.765 --> 00:32.931
Luckily, our dad is one.

00:33.000 --> 00:35.601
Yeah, people without morals suck.

00:40.307 --> 00:42.408
- Hey, baby.
- Hey, sweetie.

00:42.476 --> 00:44.676
So, what has two thumbs
and is taking you

00:44.745 --> 00:46.745
on a romantic getaway Saturday night?

00:47.848 --> 00:49.882
A-this guy.

00:49.950 --> 00:50.947
Really?

00:51.519 --> 00:52.618
What has two arms

00:52.686 --> 00:55.120
and is about to give you
the biggest hug ever?

00:55.189 --> 00:57.356
A-this girl.

00:57.425 --> 01:02.061
Hey, guys? What has two legs
and wants to jump out the window?

01:03.531 --> 01:06.298
A-this girl.

01:07.009 --> 01:08.600
This hotel is great.

01:08.669 --> 01:10.636
Olympic-size pool, private beach,

01:10.704 --> 01:13.305
four-star restaurant featuring
the tallest seafood tower

01:13.374 --> 01:14.807
on the Eastern Seaboard.

01:14.875 --> 01:16.041
- How tall is it?
- Okay.

01:16.110 --> 01:17.409
Imagine the tallest seafood tower

01:17.478 --> 01:18.710
you've ever seen on
the Eastern Seaboard.

01:18.779 --> 01:19.711
Okay.

01:19.780 --> 01:21.947
A little taller than that.

01:22.016 --> 01:24.383
Oh, I can't believe this.
What's the occasion?

01:24.452 --> 01:27.086
Let me guess. To get away from me.

01:28.210 --> 01:29.788
Get away from you?

01:29.857 --> 01:31.657
- A hundred percent.
- Uh-huh.

01:31.725 --> 01:34.059
Yeah, well,
it doesn't matter why you're going.

01:34.128 --> 01:35.461
You're going,

01:35.529 --> 01:38.130
which means I finally get
to have this place to myself.

01:40.167 --> 01:45.504
Isn't it funny when the animals
think that they run the zoo?

01:45.573 --> 01:47.005
I'll ask my parents to watch her.

01:47.074 --> 01:48.874
That's insane. It's only one night.

01:48.943 --> 01:50.209
I can be here alone.

01:50.277 --> 01:52.811
The Purge is only one night.

01:54.348 --> 01:57.382
And a lot of people
end up dead at the end.

